1
00:00:44,244 --> 00:00:48,203
"Remember, Kanak Sharma is a
candidate backed by Radhe Bhaiyya!"

2
00:00:48,648 --> 00:00:50,843
We must elect Radhe
Bhaiyya's candidate...

3
00:00:51,117 --> 00:00:54,416
as the general secretary of
our union once again this year

4
00:00:57,957 --> 00:01:01,518
Here are the benefits if
Radhe Bhaiyya's candidate wins

5
00:01:01,795 --> 00:01:05,697
You can go watch a movie and your
attendance will still be recorded

6
00:01:06,032 --> 00:01:08,500
You can carry notes to cheat
in the exams

7
00:01:08,735 --> 00:01:12,034
No action will be taken
for winking at pretty girls

8
00:01:12,939 --> 00:01:15,373
The famous dance party
from Delhi has already arrived...

9
00:01:15,608 --> 00:01:17,974
all arrangements for the
celebration are in place

10
00:01:18,111 --> 00:01:20,409
We're only waiting for
the results to be declared

11
00:01:21,948 --> 00:01:24,416
I've spent so much
in this election

12
00:01:24,851 --> 00:01:29,015
"If I lose this election,
I'll have to commit suicide"

13
00:01:29,456 --> 00:01:31,424
"Hey, Hemant bhaiyya...
why will you commit suicide?"

14
00:01:31,591 --> 00:01:34,560
It's Kanak Sharma who's going to die.
I'll murder the bastard

15
00:01:34,828 --> 00:01:37,797
Are you out of your mind?
Why do you keep talking nonsense?

16
00:01:38,098 --> 00:01:40,430
Alex has told me.
I'll bump off the bastard

17
00:01:40,633 --> 00:01:43,761
"Tiwari, skip the blah-blah"

18
00:01:44,070 --> 00:01:46,004
You aren't supposed to think aloud

19
00:01:52,178 --> 00:01:53,110
Radhe!

20
00:03:00,613 --> 00:03:04,140
Sweetheart...

21
00:03:05,685 --> 00:03:07,812
sweetheart...

22
00:03:08,521 --> 00:03:11,888
"my heart says, sweetheart..."

23
00:03:12,325 --> 00:03:14,486
come and meet me...

24
00:03:14,928 --> 00:03:17,488
don't ever go far away from me

25
00:03:31,578 --> 00:03:33,011
"No, no, no..."

26
00:03:33,179 --> 00:03:35,545
I'm not falling in love...

27
00:03:35,782 --> 00:03:38,114
don't steal my heart...

28
00:03:38,318 --> 00:03:40,878
don't get closer to me

29
00:04:20,260 --> 00:04:23,354
"Look, let me tell you..."

30
00:04:25,131 --> 00:04:30,364
"in love, when you say no,
it means yes"

31
00:04:38,077 --> 00:04:42,605
"Pretty girls' excuses are ages old,
no one has ever figured them out"

32
00:04:43,116 --> 00:04:45,607
"They won't say a word,
their eyes do the talking..."

33
00:04:45,885 --> 00:04:48,410
and they steal our hearts

34
00:05:31,998 --> 00:05:35,957
You'd better admit it...

35
00:05:36,936 --> 00:05:41,873
"those who fall in love,
shed tears"

36
00:05:49,816 --> 00:05:52,478
"Some gain, some lose,
some smile, some cry..."

37
00:05:52,719 --> 00:05:54,846
"some awake,
some sleep every moment"

38
00:05:55,088 --> 00:05:57,488
"It stokes the fires,
it causes you to pine..."

39
00:05:57,757 --> 00:06:00,123
it torments you so

40
00:06:00,660 --> 00:06:02,890
"No, no, no..."

41
00:06:05,732 --> 00:06:07,097
Sweetheart...

42
00:06:07,266 --> 00:06:09,427
"my heart says, sweetheart..."

43
00:06:09,836 --> 00:06:12,236
come and meet me...

44
00:06:12,505 --> 00:06:14,632
don't ever go far away from me

45
00:08:08,454 --> 00:08:11,423
"The first breeze of dawn,
awakens the world..."

46
00:08:11,691 --> 00:08:15,092
the bees have started to hum...

47
00:08:15,361 --> 00:08:18,762
the birds take to their wings...

48
00:08:18,965 --> 00:08:22,093
"colourful decorations
mark every courtyard"

49
00:08:22,401 --> 00:08:25,564
For blessings...

50
00:08:26,105 --> 00:08:29,131
for fulfillment...

51
00:08:29,609 --> 00:08:36,071
"at Your feet, Radha offers
flowers, O Krishna"

52
00:08:37,183 --> 00:08:41,244
"You are the one
in my heart..."

53
00:08:42,622 --> 00:08:44,988
O Krishna...

54
00:08:47,727 --> 00:08:54,826
The colourful Krishna

55
00:09:12,018 --> 00:09:15,146
"I'm crazed in love,
I have lost my senses..."

56
00:09:15,555 --> 00:09:18,615
"You are the one
I am devoted to"

57
00:09:19,058 --> 00:09:21,822
"At Your doorstep,
all day and night..."

58
00:09:22,295 --> 00:09:25,492
"it's Your name
I always chant"

59
00:09:25,898 --> 00:09:29,231
"Whatever I possess,
is Yours..."

60
00:09:29,602 --> 00:09:32,628
"to You, I dedicate my life"

61
00:09:33,072 --> 00:09:39,875
"at Your feet, Radha offers
flowers, O Krishna"

62
00:09:40,913 --> 00:09:45,213
"You are the one
in my heart..."

63
00:09:45,918 --> 00:09:48,887
O Krishna...

64
00:09:53,092 --> 00:09:56,550
The sound of your daughter's
melodious voice every morning...

65
00:09:56,996 --> 00:09:59,897
erases all our worries

66
00:10:01,133 --> 00:10:03,897
"You finished your 12th. What have you
planned to do next, my child?"

67
00:10:04,303 --> 00:10:07,898
She's going to attend college now.
- What will she gain in college?

68
00:10:08,174 --> 00:10:10,472
She's going to be married after all

69
00:10:10,776 --> 00:10:14,940
My son-in-law to-be has expressed
the wish that she studies further

70
00:10:15,681 --> 00:10:17,649
"I see. Is that true, Rameshwar?"

71
00:10:18,284 --> 00:10:23,244
"Yes, Uncle. All I could learn
at the tutelage was the Vedas"

72
00:10:23,990 --> 00:10:26,458
At least she must be a graduate

73
00:10:26,892 --> 00:10:29,952
So you want a wife
who speaks English!

74
00:10:30,997 --> 00:10:33,557
"But you know how things are
at the college, don't you?"

75
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:36,628
Kids in Agra study less
and watch movies more

76
00:10:36,936 --> 00:10:40,804
Nirjara is not like that.
And she has Indu for company

77
00:10:41,240 --> 00:10:43,174
She'll take the 7:34 a.m.
Frontier Mail every morning

78
00:10:43,409 --> 00:10:46,003
The college is near the station.
As soon as her classes are over...

79
00:10:46,278 --> 00:10:49,008
she'll take the
16:34 express train back

80
00:10:49,849 --> 00:10:52,818
Away from a world of hatred...

81
00:10:53,152 --> 00:10:56,019
in a world of love...

82
00:10:56,288 --> 00:11:00,247
"may you find happiness,
my friend..."

83
00:11:01,494 --> 00:11:06,955
When an animals kill man...

84
00:11:14,440 --> 00:11:19,343
"And now man has
slain an animal..."

85
00:11:21,113 --> 00:11:24,014
why is the world quiet?

86
00:11:24,850 --> 00:11:27,341
Give me that pickle

87
00:11:30,122 --> 00:11:33,819
I'm told there was a furore yesterday.
You got into a fight at the college

88
00:11:34,126 --> 00:11:37,027
"Fight? No, brother.
I broke their legs"

89
00:11:37,463 --> 00:11:41,627
"If I had not got there on time,
Alex's men would have killed Kanak"

90
00:11:42,068 --> 00:11:44,832
Why do you need to interfere
in someone else's affairs?

91
00:11:45,137 --> 00:11:49,540
"He's a friend. Would I remain silent,
if someone came to beat you up?"

92
00:11:50,276 --> 00:11:52,710
"Besides, it's my college"

93
00:11:53,112 --> 00:11:56,741
It was! How many years is it
since you passed out of college?

94
00:11:57,249 --> 00:12:00,082
But you still hang out there.
For no rhyme or reason

95
00:12:01,053 --> 00:12:03,681
Will you spend the life of a vagabond
or find some work to do?

96
00:12:04,056 --> 00:12:06,149
Enough. Let him have
the breakfast in peace

97
00:12:06,392 --> 00:12:09,828
"Give me a puri, sister-in-law.
- Why one? Help yourself to 40"

98
00:12:10,529 --> 00:12:13,362
Feed him the free food and make
a stronger bull out of him

99
00:12:13,766 --> 00:12:15,734
So he can keep attacking everyone!

100
00:12:19,105 --> 00:12:23,974
"Here's your puri, your bread...
and your milk"

101
00:12:27,113 --> 00:12:29,081
Don't waste the food

102
00:12:32,752 --> 00:12:34,720
Radhe...
- No

103
00:12:35,020 --> 00:12:36,885
"Listen, Radhe...
- No, sister-in-law"

104
00:12:37,289 --> 00:12:41,089
See that? You made him get up
while he was eating!

105
00:12:41,460 --> 00:12:45,089
The skies haven't fallen.
You're the one who has spoilt him

106
00:12:45,798 --> 00:12:47,766
He goes around with that
horrible hair of his...

107
00:12:48,134 --> 00:12:50,898
and makes a few others
hang out with him too

108
00:12:52,171 --> 00:12:54,537
I don't know what he's
going to do in life

109
00:12:59,845 --> 00:13:01,870
Radhe's an old student
of the college

110
00:13:03,249 --> 00:13:06,082
He rags the new students
with his friends

111
00:13:06,485 --> 00:13:09,181
Don't look at them!
Just keep walking

112
00:13:10,122 --> 00:13:12,750
"Look, Radhe.
There's a fresher with Indu"

113
00:13:15,394 --> 00:13:16,622
Listen

114
00:13:23,068 --> 00:13:24,592
Come here

115
00:13:27,106 --> 00:13:29,939
Not you. Go to your class
and get on with your studies

116
00:13:36,515 --> 00:13:37,709
First year?

117
00:13:42,354 --> 00:13:44,322
B.A. Pass course

118
00:13:46,192 --> 00:13:48,558
Can't you say good morning
to your seniors?

119
00:13:50,563 --> 00:13:53,157
Not like that. Say it like
an attentive soldier

120
00:14:01,273 --> 00:14:03,764
Keep saluting me like that
every time you pass by

121
00:14:04,243 --> 00:14:06,143
All right.
- What's that?

122
00:14:16,188 --> 00:14:18,816
And what's this?
- A peacock feather

123
00:14:19,191 --> 00:14:21,751
I can see that. But why have you
kept it in a book?

124
00:14:21,994 --> 00:14:25,157
"Kept in a notebook,
it doubles"

125
00:14:25,931 --> 00:14:27,899
Must be laying eggs!

126
00:14:34,406 --> 00:14:36,340
What's in the box?

127
00:14:42,448 --> 00:14:44,678
Wow! Puri and a vegetable dish

128
00:14:49,255 --> 00:14:50,483
Nice

129
00:14:55,261 --> 00:14:57,729
"No, don't wipe your hands
on my shirt!"

130
00:14:58,264 --> 00:15:00,027
"What are you doing, Radhe!"

131
00:15:03,202 --> 00:15:05,966
Don't wipe it with that.
It'll be a sin

132
00:15:25,791 --> 00:15:29,227
What's your name?
- Nirjara Rao

133
00:15:30,362 --> 00:15:34,230
Meaning?
- Meaning? It's my name

134
00:15:35,267 --> 00:15:37,633
It's very a difficult name.
So I asked for the meaning

135
00:15:38,304 --> 00:15:40,238
I don't know

136
00:15:40,572 --> 00:15:43,564
Who named you?
- My mother did

137
00:15:44,176 --> 00:15:46,610
So ask your mother.
- She's dead

138
00:15:50,416 --> 00:15:52,680
Is your father alive?
- Yes

139
00:15:53,452 --> 00:15:55,682
So ask him when you
come tomorrow

140
00:15:56,822 --> 00:15:59,290
All right.
- Thanks

141
00:16:02,528 --> 00:16:04,496
You saved me from sinning

142
00:16:07,266 --> 00:16:09,029
The lunch-box

143
00:16:20,312 --> 00:16:25,272
"When that peacock feather doubles,
give me one!"

144
00:16:38,497 --> 00:16:42,297
"Father, why did Ma
name me Nirjara?"

145
00:16:45,637 --> 00:16:48,299
Because your mother
loved my mother

146
00:16:48,707 --> 00:16:52,006
Your grandma.
Her name was Nirjara Devi too

147
00:16:52,378 --> 00:16:54,608
"What does it mean, father?"

148
00:16:55,047 --> 00:16:57,345
Why do you need to know today?

149
00:16:57,716 --> 00:17:03,279
"Tell me, father. Everybody asks me.
They even tease me"

150
00:17:05,591 --> 00:17:07,559
Nirjara means...

151
00:17:17,336 --> 00:17:18,530
Money?

152
00:17:21,073 --> 00:17:22,597
Here you are

153
00:17:30,382 --> 00:17:33,010
Chandu... give her a cup of tea

154
00:17:33,385 --> 00:17:34,852
"Very well, Radhe bhaiyya"

155
00:17:37,389 --> 00:17:38,913
Nut!

156
00:17:40,392 --> 00:17:42,360
Have patience.
I'm giving it to you

157
00:17:43,395 --> 00:17:45,693
Leave that alone.
What are you doing?

158
00:17:49,001 --> 00:17:50,696
Here you are...

159
00:17:51,403 --> 00:17:53,166
stop bothering me

160
00:18:59,872 --> 00:19:02,739
"Forgive me, Radhe!
It was a mistake!"

161
00:19:03,108 --> 00:19:08,410
I'll never tease a girl again!
I beg at your feet

162
00:19:08,847 --> 00:19:11,748
Please forgive me...
just once!

163
00:19:19,458 --> 00:19:20,425
Drink

164
00:19:21,593 --> 00:19:23,686
Drink it up. Go on

165
00:19:27,466 --> 00:19:30,765
"Binti, if you're going upstairs,
wake up your uncle"

166
00:19:31,470 --> 00:19:34,098
"Let him sleep, Papa.
Today's a Sunday"

167
00:19:34,506 --> 00:19:37,100
"Today's his birthday, silly!
- Birthday!"

168
00:19:37,376 --> 00:19:41,278
Wake him up quickly. We'll get ready
and go to Brindavan for prayers

169
00:19:46,518 --> 00:19:47,644
"How much money, mister?"

170
00:19:47,786 --> 00:19:50,482
"No, sir... how can we take any money
from Radhe bhaiyya?"

171
00:19:58,564 --> 00:19:59,895
"Hello, Radhe bhaiyya!"

172
00:20:04,770 --> 00:20:07,261
See your brother-in-law's reputation?

173
00:20:07,673 --> 00:20:09,607
The flower seller won't
take money from him!

174
00:20:09,908 --> 00:20:12,843
People salute him out of fear.
- They respect me...

175
00:20:13,145 --> 00:20:15,545
and you don't like that either.
- Now look. These things...

176
00:20:15,814 --> 00:20:18,214
Do you want me to go away?
- How will you go away?

177
00:20:18,650 --> 00:20:22,211
You're an amazing man!
It's Radhe's birthday today

178
00:20:22,588 --> 00:20:26,547
"At least stop taunting him today.
Come, let's go"

179
00:20:27,593 --> 00:20:32,895
O Revered Guru...

180
00:20:36,435 --> 00:20:40,895
deign to bless me

181
00:20:42,975 --> 00:20:50,939
"Grant unto me
knowledge and education"

182
00:21:28,720 --> 00:21:32,212
"My child, make some porridge.
Rameshwar likes it"

183
00:21:32,491 --> 00:21:34,118
"Very well, father"

184
00:21:36,662 --> 00:21:38,630
In whose name is the
offering to be made?

185
00:21:38,764 --> 00:21:41,198
In the name of Radhe Mohan

186
00:21:46,104 --> 00:21:47,298
Excuse me...

187
00:21:48,707 --> 00:21:50,641
please come here

188
00:21:54,713 --> 00:21:56,681
Hello.
- Hello

189
00:21:56,915 --> 00:21:59,349
So you are the priest's daughter?

190
00:21:59,718 --> 00:22:03,154
"Yes, we are Brahmins"

191
00:22:03,855 --> 00:22:07,757
"My father says, our forefathers used
to be priests in this very temple"

192
00:22:08,126 --> 00:22:11,960
I know nothing about my forefathers.
What I do know is that...

193
00:22:12,331 --> 00:22:15,198
my great grandfather used to play
hockey for the English team

194
00:22:16,668 --> 00:22:19,330
My grandfather played hockey
with Gyanchand and Dhyanchand

195
00:22:19,604 --> 00:22:24,541
"In extras, too. My father broke
his thumb while playing football"

196
00:22:24,710 --> 00:22:26,439
So he took to selling
hockey sticks

197
00:22:26,712 --> 00:22:29,681
Is that why you beat everyone
with hockey sticks?

198
00:22:32,484 --> 00:22:34,281
What?
- What happened?

199
00:22:34,720 --> 00:22:36,449
Something in my eye

200
00:22:38,724 --> 00:22:41,022
Here... give it some heat

201
00:22:45,797 --> 00:22:48,698
You found out what your name means?
- Yes

202
00:22:49,034 --> 00:22:52,492
What is it?
- Nirjara

203
00:22:55,774 --> 00:22:59,210
Jar means death.
So Nirjara means lmmortality

204
00:23:01,513 --> 00:23:03,481
There's a religious
interpretation too

205
00:23:03,715 --> 00:23:06,946
One's soul is tied to his deeds

206
00:23:07,386 --> 00:23:12,016
Deep meditation frees the soul.
And that is called Nirjara

207
00:23:17,729 --> 00:23:19,856
Here you are.
- What's that?

208
00:23:20,065 --> 00:23:21,430
Gujia (a snack)

209
00:23:27,839 --> 00:23:30,307
Got a few more?
- Yes

210
00:23:30,575 --> 00:23:32,406
For my niece

211
00:23:35,781 --> 00:23:38,443
Where did you buy it?
- Not bought it. I myself made it

212
00:23:39,050 --> 00:23:41,018
Both are nice

213
00:23:41,319 --> 00:23:43,514
The Gujia and your name too

214
00:23:43,989 --> 00:23:45,752
Your name is nice too

215
00:23:46,792 --> 00:23:50,091
Radhe Mohan is another name
for Lord Krishna. You know that?

216
00:23:53,799 --> 00:23:55,426
"Your attention,
ladies and gentlemen!"

217
00:23:55,634 --> 00:23:57,761
"She first said"ras"(juice)"

218
00:23:58,069 --> 00:24:00,299
"She then said"gul"(rose)"

219
00:24:00,705 --> 00:24:02,400
"And then she said"le"(take)"

220
00:24:06,778 --> 00:24:10,737
"Listen, ras, gul and le..."

221
00:24:11,316 --> 00:24:14,752
that's how she broke up
the rasgollah!

222
00:24:17,789 --> 00:24:20,087
Thank you very much

223
00:24:32,637 --> 00:24:35,572
She's now going to bore us
to death with a poem

224
00:24:40,846 --> 00:24:42,780
Clear your throat!

225
00:24:50,188 --> 00:24:52,816
"Stars are nothing
but the Sun of the night"

226
00:24:53,358 --> 00:24:55,485
"Like the West
is also East"

227
00:24:55,894 --> 00:24:58,829
We get that!
So what happens next?

228
00:25:02,868 --> 00:25:05,302
"Go on, Nirjara"

229
00:25:05,837 --> 00:25:08,203
They won't let me speak

230
00:25:08,607 --> 00:25:13,806
"North in South,
East in West... so what's new?"

231
00:25:30,128 --> 00:25:34,565
I've taken the trouble
of coming to the stage...

232
00:25:35,233 --> 00:25:37,827
because I've liked her
poem very much

233
00:25:38,203 --> 00:25:43,835
"And since I have liked it,
you will like it too. Get that?"

234
00:25:44,809 --> 00:25:48,540
Those who understand will
quietly listen to the recital...

235
00:25:48,914 --> 00:25:52,213
"and those who don't,
will still sit quietly and listen"

236
00:25:53,585 --> 00:25:55,678
Everything's under control.
Please come

237
00:25:57,222 --> 00:25:58,553
Clap for her

238
00:26:04,529 --> 00:26:06,827
"Stars are nothing
but the Suns of the night"

239
00:26:07,265 --> 00:26:09,825
"Like the West
is also the East"

240
00:26:10,302 --> 00:26:12,827
"The Earth is the daughter
of the Sun..."

241
00:26:13,138 --> 00:26:15,538
"suspended on a bed
in the skies"

242
00:26:15,974 --> 00:26:18,670
"The Sun is an eye-full
of light..."

243
00:26:19,311 --> 00:26:21,245
spread everywhere around

244
00:26:22,914 --> 00:26:24,882
Where are my...

245
00:26:43,602 --> 00:26:48,232
Radhe-ji... my recital is over

246
00:28:22,067 --> 00:28:30,031
"How I love meeting you,
and talking to you"

247
