without any self-interest..."

729
01:15:13,609 --> 01:15:17,375
"helps save another person's family,
is he a bad human being?"

730
01:15:19,081 --> 01:15:21,914
"Yes, I admit he's a bit
hard and wayward"

731
01:15:22,751 --> 01:15:26,380
"For that matter,
even God lives in idols of stone"

732
01:15:27,523 --> 01:15:29,514
But don't we worship Him?

733
01:15:31,426 --> 01:15:35,089
The truth is that
he loves you very much

734
01:15:37,099 --> 01:15:38,259
True love

735
01:15:39,735 --> 01:15:44,104
Think about it.
Did he ever misbehave with you?

736
01:15:44,673 --> 01:15:46,766
Did he ever try to
take advantage of you?

737
01:15:47,476 --> 01:15:49,410
He hasn't even touched you

738
01:15:51,179 --> 01:15:54,774
You must be wondering why
I'm telling you all this

739
01:15:56,685 --> 01:16:01,987
It's because I've realised...
he's a far better human being than me

740
01:16:02,758 --> 01:16:07,752
"Better than you, better than me,
better than thousands of others"

741
01:16:10,165 --> 01:16:12,599
He can even lay down
his life for you

742
01:16:14,636 --> 01:16:19,938
Which is why Radhe Mohan is
your true companion for life

743
01:16:22,444 --> 01:16:23,604
Not me

744
01:18:04,212 --> 01:18:07,511
Take a look at me!
Have you ever seen me like this?

745
01:18:08,917 --> 01:18:13,320
I used to be so happy! But ever
since I've fallen in love with you...

746
01:18:13,755 --> 01:18:15,723
it seems as if my bad times have begun

747
01:18:17,626 --> 01:18:23,292
"I thought people who gave up their
lives for their love, were such fools"

748
01:18:23,899 --> 01:18:26,060
"But now I realise,
why they do it"

749
01:18:26,635 --> 01:18:29,126
"Rather than suffer like me,
they get their freedom in moments!"

750
01:18:31,440 --> 01:18:34,409
But you needn't worry.
I'm not dying

751
01:18:34,910 --> 01:18:38,573
"Because, if I die...
you will become a widow"

752
01:18:40,816 --> 01:18:42,784
And I can't bear to see
you being widowed

753
01:18:44,619 --> 01:18:46,280
The truth is...

754
01:19:21,056 --> 01:19:24,355
Enough! Enough!

755
01:19:26,027 --> 01:19:27,585
I feel like...

756
01:19:55,824 --> 01:20:00,659
"Now look, Nirjara...
I don't want to rape you"

757
01:20:02,697 --> 01:20:05,165
I only want two minutes from you

758
01:20:06,635 --> 01:20:09,536
I want you to hear how I feel.
That's it

759
01:20:10,705 --> 01:20:14,197
I want you to be happy.
And smiling

760
01:20:16,111 --> 01:20:17,908
You get what I'm saying?

761
01:20:23,952 --> 01:20:25,920
Everyone in the world
falls in love

762
01:20:26,955 --> 01:20:30,982
Am I the only one without a right
to love someone...

763
01:20:31,560 --> 01:20:33,528
to have someone love me?
Well?

764
01:20:35,764 --> 01:20:37,732
We'll treat you like a queen

765
01:20:38,967 --> 01:20:45,202
"I, my brother, my sister-in-law,
Binti... and all my friends..."

766
01:20:48,577 --> 01:20:50,977
That boy your father
has chosen for you...

767
01:20:55,016 --> 01:20:59,476
I'm not saying he's not a good guy.
He must be a nice chap

768
01:21:00,989 --> 01:21:05,085
Start calling him your brother.
Or make a friend out of him

769
01:21:06,895 --> 01:21:08,726
I'll accept your friend

770
01:21:10,665 --> 01:21:12,929
I want to give the priest's
daughter a nice life...

771
01:21:14,536 --> 01:21:17,130
and that priest wants to
snatch my life from me?

772
01:21:18,740 --> 01:21:21,231
"As if he's the priest,
and I'm an untouchable!"

773
01:21:25,747 --> 01:21:27,772
What future will
you have with him?

774
01:21:28,516 --> 01:21:32,976
"When I think of it,
about you and him..."

775
01:21:34,022 --> 01:21:35,990
it sends my head reeling.
Like this!

776
01:21:39,027 --> 01:21:44,192
"After listening to all this,
you must surely realise..."

777
01:21:45,033 --> 01:21:49,163
"how dearly I love you?
If you still don't get it, I..."

778
01:21:50,805 --> 01:21:52,500
I know what I'll do!

779
01:22:01,783 --> 01:22:03,978
Go away! Go away!

780
01:22:08,924 --> 01:22:13,987
"Go away, else I'll kill you.
Go!"

781
01:22:16,031 --> 01:22:18,261
But what will I do with my life then?

782
01:22:19,901 --> 01:22:22,301
I don't want to live
a moment without you

783
01:22:25,240 --> 01:22:27,333
Yes! I have forcibly
brought you here!

784
01:22:28,743 --> 01:22:31,576
"And yes, I'm indeed
screaming at you!"

785
01:22:34,082 --> 01:22:35,606
I'm threatening you!

786
01:22:37,252 --> 01:22:39,049
That's only because...

787
01:22:43,091 --> 01:22:45,389
it's because I love you very much

788
01:22:45,827 --> 01:22:51,732
Because I think you were made
only for me... only for me

789
01:22:54,102 --> 01:22:56,070
You were born for me alone

790
01:22:57,105 --> 01:23:00,472
Ask your God! Ask Him!

791
01:23:03,078 --> 01:23:10,041
"I'm going through so much of pain...
so much of misery, God!"

792
01:23:30,105 --> 01:23:31,402
Forgive me

793
01:23:34,142 --> 01:23:35,666
Do please forgive me

794
01:24:04,105 --> 01:24:09,065
"I've draped the scarf...
I dance for you"

795
01:24:20,755 --> 01:24:23,690
"I drape the scarf
and dance..."

796
01:24:24,059 --> 01:24:26,459
for I have lost my heart

797
01:24:29,030 --> 01:24:35,128
"I've fallen in love with you,
I've lost my heart to you"

798
01:24:49,517 --> 01:24:55,649
"Your love gives me a high...
I've lost my heart to you"

799
01:24:57,792 --> 01:25:03,822
"I've fallen in love with you,
I've lost my heart to you"

800
01:25:05,567 --> 01:25:09,128
"I dance, I break every promise..."

801
01:25:09,737 --> 01:25:15,175
"Every promise, I break
and dance today..."

802
01:25:51,312 --> 01:25:55,009
"My bangles speak,
my anklets say..."

803
01:25:55,450 --> 01:25:59,045
"come with the bridal palanquin
and take me away, my love"

804
01:25:59,721 --> 01:26:02,986
With henna on my palms...

805
01:26:03,825 --> 01:26:06,988
"bridal vermillion
on my forehead..."

806
01:26:07,462 --> 01:26:12,866
"I'll dress up
only for you, my love"

807
01:26:13,368 --> 01:26:20,001
"The Spring of my beauty is here...
for I have lost my heart to you"

808
01:26:21,476 --> 01:26:28,245
"I drape the scarf today
and dance for you"

809
01:27:11,559 --> 01:27:14,995
"In your name
I shall bequeath..."

810
01:27:15,730 --> 01:27:18,597
this story of my realisation

811
01:27:19,734 --> 01:27:23,329
"If we are to unite,
we shall unite..."

812
01:27:23,771 --> 01:27:27,070
not to be separated for ages

813
01:27:27,508 --> 01:27:32,070
"I have waited for years, my love"

814
01:27:33,681 --> 01:27:36,707
"Even in pining
I found succour, my love"

815
01:27:37,085 --> 01:27:40,111
I've lost my heart to you

816
01:27:41,389 --> 01:27:48,022
"I've fallen in love with you,
my heart is no longer mine"

817
01:27:49,797 --> 01:27:53,631
"Every promise, I break
and dance today..."

818
01:28:51,459 --> 01:28:54,053
So you're going to make us
shut down our business?

819
01:28:54,429 --> 01:28:57,398
You ought to have kept
your bullying ways to your college

820
01:29:26,127 --> 01:29:27,856
Get up

821
01:29:28,930 --> 01:29:31,398
"You will shut our business down, eh?
Wanna be a hero, eh?"

822
01:33:12,553 --> 01:33:15,920
"Nirjara, how can you
go on like this?"

823
01:33:20,595 --> 01:33:22,187
I want to meet him once

824
01:33:22,563 --> 01:33:23,655
What for?

825
01:33:25,833 --> 01:33:28,427
Why're you unnecessarily
bothering yourself?

826
01:33:31,472 --> 01:33:34,134
"You don't understand, Indu.
- I understand everything"

827
01:33:35,743 --> 01:33:38,906
But is there any point
in all this anymore?

828
01:33:39,780 --> 01:33:45,047
The sooner you get
him out of your mind the better

829
01:33:46,487 --> 01:33:49,923
You understand?
Let's go now. C'mon

830
01:34:18,219 --> 01:34:19,948
Get an injection! Quick!

831
01:35:00,561 --> 01:35:02,188
Where has he gone?

832
01:35:42,603 --> 01:35:44,264
He has survived

833
01:35:44,839 --> 01:35:49,299
But neither can he understand anything
nor recognise anyone

834
01:35:52,980 --> 01:35:55,847
It's really very sad but
every effort of ours...

835
01:35:56,217 --> 01:35:59,084
"to bring about an improvement in
Radhe's condition, has failed"

836
01:36:00,688 --> 01:36:02,986
That's exactly why I wish
to say something to you folks

837
01:36:04,592 --> 01:36:05,581
Of course. Please go ahead

838
01:36:05,993 --> 01:36:10,020
"Although I'm a doctor,
I still believe in God"

839
01:36:11,766 --> 01:36:14,200
Whenever I fall sick...

840
01:36:14,568 --> 01:36:18,129
my mother gives me oblations
before any other medicines

841
01:36:19,874 --> 01:36:22,809
"It has to do with devotion,
it defies logic"

842
01:36:23,677 --> 01:36:28,842
Because prayers and medicines are
both very important in our society

843
01:36:29,683 --> 01:36:30,650
Absolutely

844
01:36:31,185 --> 01:36:33,153
I was going to suggest
something of the sort

845
01:36:34,822 --> 01:36:37,188
You must've heard of Sripurdham?

846
01:36:39,794 --> 01:36:42,422
Although medical science
does not believe in it...

847
01:36:42,797 --> 01:36:48,201
Swami Sheelbhadra uses ancient
cures to heal patients

848
01:36:48,669 --> 01:36:51,263
"If medical science does not believe
it, why must you believe it?"

849
01:36:51,939 --> 01:36:57,377
Do you know? Patients are bound in
chains and treated worse than animals

850
01:36:57,945 --> 01:37:00,539
And you want to send Radhe there?
- That's because...

851
01:37:00,881 --> 01:37:05,716
"in a fit of violence, they shouldn't
hurt themselves or anyone else"

852
01:37:11,458 --> 01:37:16,191
Whatever this boy just said
is not wrong

853
01:37:17,898 --> 01:37:22,733
But it's also true that several patients
like Radhe have been cured there

854
01:37:24,605 --> 01:37:26,664
It has to do with faith
and devotion

855
01:37:28,876 --> 01:37:31,868
"You either have it,
or you don't"

856
01:37:35,950 --> 01:37:38,418
Where is Sripurdham?

857
01:37:38,953 --> 01:37:40,716
Just telephone them

858
01:37:41,055 --> 01:37:44,252
Their workers will come
and personally take Radhe away

859
01:37:49,663 --> 01:37:51,460
What are you thinking of doing?

860
01:37:52,566 --> 01:37:55,501
"What can we think of, Aslam?
We'll have to send him there"

861
01:37:55,970 --> 01:37:58,632
You take just about anyone's
advise seriously!

862
01:37:59,707 --> 01:38:03,473
He spoke in our own interests.
- Really? And what was that?

863
01:38:05,946 --> 01:38:08,244
To not take your brother back home?

864
01:38:09,850 --> 01:38:11,909
To hand him over to some
crazy ascetic?

865
01:38:12,853 --> 01:38:14,912
So that he can try his
mumbo-jumbo on him...?

866
01:38:15,723 --> 01:38:18,157
Even if it leaves your brother dead?
- Aslam!

867
01:38:19,526 --> 01:38:20,925
The doctor's trying
to save his neck...

868
01:38:21,295 --> 01:38:23,320
and these folks don't want anyone
to be a burden on them

869
01:38:24,231 --> 01:38:27,359
"If your brother is such a burden,
don't take him home!"

870
01:38:27,968 --> 01:38:31,927
"I'll take him away. I'll look
after him, I'll nurse him!"

871
01:38:33,007 --> 01:38:35,532
But I'm not letting you send
him to some ascetic's ashram!

872
01:38:36,010 --> 01:38:38,478
Let me tell you that.
And you better listen to me!

873
01:38:38,913 --> 01:38:39,937
Insolent!

874
01:38:41,782 --> 01:38:46,583
I'm the one who has pampered
these boys. It's my fault!

875
01:38:47,755 --> 01:38:50,781
"Else, could anyone
misbehave with you...?"

876
01:38:52,826 --> 01:38:54,657
"Gayatri, calm down"

877
01:38:56,030 --> 01:39:00,694
He's upset because he
loves Radhe so much

878
01:39:03,871 --> 01:39:05,361
Go and sit there

879
01:39:12,079 --> 01:39:16,539
Let him go.
Maybe it's good for Radhe

880
01:39:20,020 --> 01:39:21,487
"Look at me, Aslam"

881
01:39:22,790 --> 01:39:27,318
I can't say whether
I have understood Radhe

882
01:39:29,163 --> 01:39:34,533
But one thing I'm proud of...
he has friends like you

883
01:39:39,406 --> 01:39:41,135
"Forgive me, brother"

884
01:39:46,280 --> 01:39:49,044
You know why I'm sending you
to Sripurdham?

885
01:39:49,850 --> 01:39:52,318
Because I'm fed up of you!
That's it!

886
01:39:53,821 --> 01:39:57,222
I'm sick of your
fights and brawls

887
01:39:58,959 --> 01:40:00,722
I'm tired of reasoning with you!

888
01:40:01,695 --> 01:40:04,858
I now want you to get out
of my sight...

889
01:40:05,265 --> 01:40:09,395
so I can breathe easily!
Do you hear that?

890
01:40:11,038 --> 01:40:13,370
What are you doing?

891
01:40:20,147 --> 01:40:24,777
Look... I've been scolding him.
And he doesn't even talk back

892
01:40:28,756 --> 01:40:34,786
Radhe... I'll sit with you
at the station henceforth

893
01:40:35,162 --> 01:40:38,529
We'll sit outside the college.
We'll act like bullies...

894
01:40:39,166 --> 01:40:40,793
I'll join you too

895
01:40:41,935 --> 01:40:47,134
Just get well...
please get well

896
01:40:57,217 --> 01:40:59,981
"Get well, please"

897
01:41:04,191 --> 01:41:05,453
Sister-in-law...

898
01:41:09,163 --> 01:41:11,461
the van has arrived
to take Radhe away

899
01:42:57,304 --> 01:43:05,211
Why does this happen in love?

900
01:43:57,064 --> 01:44:01,558
Why does loyalty...

901
01:44:02,069 --> 01:44:05,266
not beget loyalty?

902
01:44:06,073 --> 01:44:10,908
Why are good wishes...

903
01:44:11,345 --> 01:44:14,508
not answered with good wishes?

904
01:44:15,349 --> 01:44:19,979
Why is happiness...

905
01:44:20,387 --> 01:44:23,652
not reciprocated with joy?

906
01:44:24,858 --> 01:44:29,818
What does this happen in love?

907
01:45:00,627 --> 01:45:02,822
Love makes you weep...

908
01:45:03,297 --> 01:45:05,527
it makes you forget the world

909
01:45:05,932 --> 01:45:11,336
"It makes you pine,
it makes you restless"

910
01:45:11,938 --> 01:45:15,897
What has love turned people into?

911
01:45:17,411 --> 01:45:19,345
They met their beloveds...

912
01:45:20,080 --> 01:45:22,014
and separated

913
01:45:22,516 --> 01:45:27,180
"All they got was misery
even in Spring..."

914
01:45:27,688 --> 01:45:32,648
"their lifetimes being spent,
waiting for their beloveds"

915
01:45:37,164 --> 01:45:45,401
"Why doesn't a smile
beget a smile?"

916
01:45:46,273 --> 01:45:54,772
"Why isn't loyalty
greeted with loyalty?"

917
01:46:37,991 --> 01:46:41,859
"Time never comes
to a standstill"

918
01:46:43,230 --> 01:46:47,166
Do memories ever cease?

919
01:46:48,368 --> 01:46:52,771
When medicines cease to heal...

920
01:46:53,540 --> 01:46:57,977
what does one do?

921
01:47:02,783 --> 01:47:10,451
"Why isn't joy
greeted with joy?"

922
01:47:12,225 --> 01:47:20,132
"Why isn't loyalty
paid back with loyalty?"

923
01:47:41,354 --> 01:47:42,514
Chander...

924
01:47:44,724 --> 01:47:49,684
no one's telling me how Radhe is.
Where have they taken him?

925
01:47:50,564 --> 01:47:52,327
But you surely know?

926
01:47:53,333 --> 01:47:55,858
Girls are not allowed there

927
01:47:56,570 --> 01:48:00,131
But Radhe will be all right
Don't worry

928
01:48:00,540 --> 01:48:03,737
I've put in a word to God
and He too has told me...

929
01:48:04,177 --> 01:48:05,769
that Radhe will be all right

930
01:48:07,547 --> 01:48:09,481
Praise the Lord...

931
01:49:07,374 --> 01:49:11,538
"See how ardently she
is praying, Rameshwar"

932
01:49:15,615 --> 01:49:17,276
I wonder who's ill

933
01:49:17,617 --> 01:49:20,916
Has she had something to eat?
- No

934
01:49:21,788 --> 01:49:24,916
She's been praying since this morning.
- This morning?

935
01:49:25,525 --> 01:49:29,393
"Yes, a boy in her college is...
- Is...?"

936
01:49:31,431 --> 01:49:34,730
He's lying in the ashram
at Sripur

937
01:49:41,675 --> 01:49:43,768
This girl is just like her mother

938
01:49:44,678 --> 01:49:48,307
She's been fasting and
praying for a stranger

939
01:49:48,682 --> 01:49:51,810
"He's no stranger, Guruji.
- No...?"

940
01:49:58,725 --> 01:50:03,185
That boy belongs to Nirjara's college
and Nirjara...

941
01:50:03,630 --> 01:50:07,964
Yes? Go on.
- She's in love with him

942
01:50:43,503 --> 01:50:48,941
"Nirjara, is what
Rameshwar saying... true?"

943
01:50:54,981 --> 01:50:56,107
"Yes, father"

944
01:50:58,685 --> 01:51:00,118
Lord!

945
01:51:02,422 --> 01:51:07,291
"I've committed no sin, father.
I've done nothing wrong"

946
01:51:07,761 --> 01:51:10,025
What is this if not wrong?

947
01:51:11,765 --> 01:51:14,063
Maybe that boy has
done us favours

948
01:51:15,435 --> 01:51:18,063
He has helped your sister
settle down again

949
01:51:18,638 --> 01:51:21,300
But will you entrust
yourself to him for that?

950
01:51:21,808 --> 01:51:23,742
"I already have, father"

951
01:51:26,046 --> 01:51:28,071
I've given him my heart

952
01:51:31,518 --> 01:51:33,782
And my heart isn't
outside my body

953
01:54:37,871 --> 01:54:40,840
How can you afford
to be so disheartened?

954
01:54:42,008 --> 01:54:47,537
I wasn't ever polite with him

955
01:54:51,017 --> 01:54:52,541
Don't worry

956
01:54:54,020 --> 01:54:57,581
He... he'll return soon

957
01:54:58,925 --> 01:55:01,917
Our Radhe will return.
Just you see

958
01:55:39,899 --> 01:55:40,991
Swamiji...

959
01:56:03,790 --> 01:56:04,779
Swamiji...!

960
01:56:10,029 --> 01:56:11,326
Rameshwarji...

961
01:56:17,036 --> 01:56:18,003
Rameshwarji...

962
01:56:19,038 --> 01:56:20,335
Who is it?

963
01:56:30,249 --> 01:56:35,209
Rameshwarji... please take me
to Radhe. Just once

964
01:56:40,093 --> 01:56:42,618
I'll remain indebted to you
all my life

965
01:56:48,968 --> 01:56:51,402
"All right, we'll leave
in the morning"

966
02:01:35,354 --> 02:01:39,188
Mahantji... Nirjara has gone to
Sripurdham with Rameshwar

967
02:01:39,592 --> 02:01:42,220
A boy from his college
has been admitted there

968
02:01:42,595 --> 02:01:44,722
She said she would
return by nightfall

969
02:01:45,298 --> 02:01:47,061
Here are the keys to your house

970
02:01:48,134 --> 02:01:52,070
The priest is here to meet you.
- Priest?

971
02:01:52,438 --> 02:01:54,633
"Yes, Nirjara's father"

972
02:02:27,506 --> 02:02:29,440
"You've seen what state
he's in, haven't you?"

973
02:02:32,278 --> 02:02:35,441
Do you think we didn't want to
have a daughter-in-law like you?

974
02:02:37,550 --> 02:02:42,453
But perhaps that is
not possible anymore

975
02:02:45,358 --> 02:02:47,121
Had my brother been all right...

976
02:02:47,493 --> 02:02:50,792
I'd have begged your father
for your hand

977
02:02:52,431 --> 02:02:58,995
But to think of him now
and to hope that he...

978
02:03:05,277 --> 02:03:11,512
it's futile. It's over
It's all over

979
02:03:18,758 --> 02:03:22,956
The things man thinks of doing...
and what turns out to be

980
02:03:29,235 --> 02:03:36,664
It isn't right to think only of your
happiness and cause anguish to others

981
02:03:38,677 --> 02:03:45,583
"You know, your father has thought
of nothing but your welfare"

982
02:03:48,354 --> 02:03:50,322
He's the father who has
given you life

983
02:03:52,558 --> 02:03:55,049
You mustn't be obstinate
and drive him to death

984
02:03:59,365 --> 02:04:01,128
"Give him his due, please"

985
02:04:28,294 --> 02:04:30,854
"When is it auspicious to
hold the wedding, holy sir?"

986
02:04:31,263 --> 02:04:38,533
"Friday, July 10 is an
auspicious date for the wedding"

987
02:04:46,612 --> 02:04:50,912
It's all over. Looks like Nirjara
is going to be married to Rameshwar

988
02:04:51,750 --> 02:04:56,380
Why're you hitting him?
- He always talks nonsense!

989
02:04:57,389 --> 02:04:59,880
Radhe's not yet dead.
He's just ill

990
02:05:02,328 --> 02:05:05,229
Wait and see. He'll come back
as soon as he gets well

991
02:05:05,598 --> 02:05:08,260
And when will that be? When?
After the marriage is over?

992
02:05:08,567 --> 02:05:11,798
"No, he'll come soon"

993
02:05:13,572 --> 02:05:15,870
I have a feeling
he's coming back soon

994
02:05:52,678 --> 02:05:54,612
Where are you going?
Get back there

995
02:10:15,874 --> 02:10:21,574
God alone knows
what drove her to consume poison!

996
02:11:57,075 --> 02:12:01,944
"Even in death, we shall
not break our promise"

997
02:12:04,016 --> 02:12:08,976
"We will never part
from each other"

998
02:12:11,023 --> 02:12:15,983
"Ours is a relationship
spanning many births"

999
02:12:17,763 --> 02:12:22,325
"Who has ever separated
life from the body?"

1000
02:12:25,270 --> 02:12:31,175
Without you...

1001
02:12:32,077 --> 02:12:38,744
"without you, this ocean
has no shore, my love"

1002
02:12:53,966 --> 02:13:00,064
"In your name, I have bequeathed
my entire life, my love"

1003
02:13:09,081 --> 02:13:14,178
"My entire life, my love"

